FBIS4-4073 "drchi082_p_94007" FBIS-CHI-94-082 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 Central-South Region Investment, Trade Flourish in Guangzhou Investment, Trade Flourish in Guangzhou HK2704143994 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in Mandarin 0400 GMT 17 Apr 94 HK2704143994 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [Text] Guangzhou's foreign-related economy and foreign trade have been developing in a healthy way. By the end of March this year, another group of 699 contracts, using foreign capital valued at $3.38 billion, had been signed throughout the city, an increase 4.6 percent over the same period last year. In addition, foreign capital totalling $489 million actually had been used, 80.8 percent more than in the same period last year. The city's export volume reached $820 million, registering a 23 percent increase over the corresponding period last year. Last year, the development of Guangzhou's foreign-related economy and foreign trade were marked by the following five main features: 1) The actual amount of invested capital increased by a greater margin owing to direct investment by foreign businessmen; 2) The scale of investment was larger and the quality of investment projects was higher; 3) The areas in which foreign businessmen made direct investments achieved diversified development; 4) There was a smooth transition of foreign trade and export to a new system, and a faster increase in exports, changing the previous situation of insufficient exports at the beginning of the year, and excessive increases at the end of the year; 5) New progress was made in opening up a diversified market. During the first quarter, Guangzhou examined and approved the establishment of three enterprises from abroad, and six enterprises were registered.
